From 3ecf4e18db0d6e94aabdf20fd9be5bcce51767b8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 11:01:30 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): add `runs doctor` journal health checker with
 mechanical repair (FR-E83)

Add `flowai-workflow runs doctor --workflow <dir> --run <id>` to diagnose a
run's durability artifacts (journal.jsonl, run directory, runs/.lock) and apply
only safe mechanical repairs.

Checks (every problem reported, grouped by severity; exit 0 iff no ERRORs):
- journal integrity (lexical scan): missing/non-final-unparsable=ERROR, torn
  final line/duplicate event_id=WARNING, unknown kind/non-monotonic seq=ERROR
- replay invariants via the EXISTING replayer (no second replayer):
  events-after-terminal, undeclared-node lifecycle, attempt_completed without a
  matching attempt_started, cost-sum divergence
- filesystem cross-check: orphan dir=WARNING, missing declared dir=ERROR,
  stale runs/.lock=WARNING

--repair applies only torn-line drop (journal.jsonl.bak backup + atomic
tmp-write+rename) and stale-lock removal; refuses (nothing modified) on a live
lock or any error beyond the torn line. --json emits a findings list; the
subcommand appears in --help.

Diagnostics live in a testable src/state/doctor.ts core; cli.ts is a thin
parse/print/exit wrapper. Reuses state/run-journal/lock helpers (exports
isProcessAlive); no new deps. Registers FR-E83 in the SRS + index + SDS + README.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
