+### 3.83 FR-E83: Runs Doctor Journal Health Checker
+
+- **Description:** `flowai-workflow runs doctor --workflow <dir> --run <id>`
+  diagnoses a run's durability artifacts and can apply ONLY safe mechanical
+  repairs. The append-only `journal.jsonl` is the sole recovery record (FR-E69)
+  and the strict replayer aborts on the first defect; doctor turns that opaque
+  failure into a graded report and a narrow, reversible fix path. It only
+  orchestrates and inspects — the EXISTING replayer (`replayRunJournal`) stays
+  the single source of replay truth (no second replayer).
+
+  **Checks (every problem reported, grouped ERROR / WARNING / OK):**
+  - *Journal integrity* (lexical line scan): missing file (ERROR); non-final
+    unparsable line (ERROR); truncated/garbage FINAL line with no trailing
+    newline — the crash artifact the writer already tolerates (WARNING);
+    unknown event `kind` (ERROR); non-monotonic `seq` (ERROR); duplicate
+    `event_id` (WARNING — the replayer dedupes it).
+  - *Replay invariants* (via `replayRunJournal`): events after a terminal run
+    event (ERROR); node-lifecycle events for a node never declared (ERROR);
+    `attempt_completed` without a matching `attempt_started` (ERROR); replayed
+    `total_cost_usd` diverging from the per-node `cost_usd` sum (ERROR).
+  - *Filesystem cross-check*: an on-disk node directory no journal event
+    mentions = orphan (WARNING); a journal-declared directory missing on disk
+    (ERROR); a `runs/.lock` naming this run whose recorded PID is dead = stale
+    lock (WARNING).
+
+  **Output / exit:** human report grouped by severity, or `--json` (findings
+  list of `{severity, code, message, evidence}`). Exit 0 iff no ERROR, else 1.
+
+  **`--repair`** applies ONLY: drop a torn final journal line (back up to
+  `journal.jsonl.bak`, then atomic tmp-write + rename without the torn line)
+  and remove a stale lock — each reported. It REFUSES (clear error, nothing
+  modified) when the run is active (live lock) or the journal has any error
+  beyond the torn final line (no guessed semantic repairs).
+
+  **Constraints:** no new dependencies; reuses `src/state/` path/lock helpers
+  (`getRunDir`, `getJournalPath`, `defaultLockPath`, `readLockInfo`,
+  `releaseLock`, `isProcessAlive`); one `--run` per invocation; flags only (no
+  interactive prompts); no journal compaction beyond the torn final line.
