+### `src/state/doctor.ts` — shape
+
+```ts
+export type DoctorSeverity = "error" | "warning";
+export interface DoctorFinding {
+  severity: DoctorSeverity;
+  code: string;       // stable kebab id, e.g. "journal-torn-tail"
+  message: string;    // human-readable detail
+  evidence: string;   // path (journal/dir/lock) the finding refers to
+}
+export interface RepairOutcome {
+  refused: boolean;
+  reason?: string;        // set iff refused; nothing was modified
+  applied: string[];      // human-readable actions performed
+  backupPath?: string;    // journal.jsonl.bak when the torn line was dropped
+}
+export interface DoctorReport {
+  run_id: string;
+  run_dir: string;
+  ok: boolean;            // no ERROR findings
+  findings: DoctorFinding[];
+  repair?: RepairOutcome; // present only with --repair
+}
+export interface DoctorOptions {
+  workflowDir: string; runId: string; repair?: boolean;
+}
+export async function diagnoseRun(o: DoctorOptions): Promise<{
+  report: DoctorReport; internals: { tornTail?: {validByteLength:number};
+  staleLock?: {lockPath:string}; runActive: boolean; hardErrors: boolean; }
+}>;
+export async function runDoctor(o: DoctorOptions): Promise<DoctorReport>;
+export function formatReport(r: DoctorReport): string;   // grouped human text
+export function reportToJson(r: DoctorReport): unknown;   // machine shape
+```
+
+### Phase a — journal integrity (lexical line scan; not replay)
+
+Read `getJournalPath(getRunDir(runId, workflowDir))`.
+- `NotFound` → ERROR `journal-missing`; skip phase b (cannot replay).
+- Split on `\n`; track `endedWithNewline` and per-line byte `lineStart`.
+  For each non-empty line, `JSON.parse`:
+  - parse fails AND it is the final line AND `!endedWithNewline` → WARNING
+    `journal-torn-tail`; record `validByteLength = bytes(content.slice(0,
+    lineStart))` (== the replayer's own partial-tail offset) for repair.
+  - parse fails otherwise → ERROR `journal-unparsable-line` (mid-file garbage;
+    sets `hardErrors`, which suppresses replay so we never double-report).
+  - parse OK → check `kind ∈ RunJournalEventKind` set, else ERROR
+    `journal-unknown-kind`; if `seq <= prevSeq` → ERROR
+    `journal-nonmonotonic-seq`; if `event_id` already seen → WARNING
+    `journal-duplicate-event-id`.
+
+### Phase b — replay invariants (via `replayRunJournal` only)
+
+Skip if `hardErrors` (a non-final parse error makes replay throw — already
+reported). Otherwise `try { replay = await replayRunJournal(runDir) }`; a
+throw with no prior hard error (missing `run_started` / mixed-run) → ERROR
+`replay-failed`. On success, inspect `replay.events` (deduped, in order) +
+`replay.state`:
+- iterate events; after the first terminal kind
+  (`run_completed`/`run_failed`/`run_aborted`), any later event → ERROR
+  `event-after-terminal`.
+- `declared = Set(node_id from node_declared)`; any
+  `node_(started|completed|failed|waiting|skipped)` whose `node_id ∉ declared`
+  → ERROR `undeclared-node-lifecycle`.
+- key attempts by `node_id::iteration`; any `attempt_completed` with no
+  matching `attempt_started` key → ERROR `attempt-completed-without-start`.
+- cost: per node, take the flat metadata `cost_usd` from its last
+  node-lifecycle event (the mirror the replayer does NOT fold into the total —
+  the replayer rolls up `event.node.cost_usd`); sum and compare to
+  `replay.state.total_cost_usd ?? 0`. `|Δ| > 1e-9` → ERROR
+  `cost-sum-divergence`. (Healthy journals keep the two cost fields equal, so
+  this never false-fires; it catches a tampered/internally-inconsistent
+  journal — the only way the two can disagree.)
+
+### Phase c — filesystem cross-check
+
+- `declaredRel` = relative-to-runDir paths from `node_directory_declared`
+  (rebase `node_dir` by stripping through the `runId` segment) ∪ from
+  `node_declared` (`phase ? "<phase>/<id>" : "<id>"`).
+- On-disk: walk `runDir` for leaf directories, skipping reserved top-level
+  names (`logs`, `worktree`, `.hitl-inbox`, `.git`); a dir whose rel path is in
+  `declaredRel` is terminal (not recursed). Leaf rel ∉ `declaredRel` → WARNING
+  `orphan-node-dir`. `declaredRel` entry absent on disk → ERROR
+  `missing-declared-dir`.
+- Lock: `readLockInfo(defaultLockPath(workflowDir))` (absent/corrupt → no lock
+  finding). If `info.run_id === runId`: PID alive → `runActive=true` (no
+  finding — a running run is normal); PID dead → WARNING `stale-lock` +
+  `staleLock` internal flag.
+
+### Repair (`--repair`)
+
+After diagnosis, apply ONLY when safe:
+- `runActive` → `RepairOutcome{refused, reason:"run is active (pid …)"}`,
+  modify nothing.
+- any ERROR finding (all errors are "beyond the torn final line", which is a
+  WARNING) → refuse, reason "journal has errors beyond the torn final line —
+  no semantic repairs", modify nothing.
+- else: if `tornTail` → copy journal to `journal.jsonl.bak`, write
+  `content[0:validByteLength]` to `journal.jsonl.tmp`, `Deno.rename` over the
+  original (atomic); `applied += "removed torn final journal line"`. If
+  `staleLock` → `releaseLock(lockPath)`; `applied += "removed stale lock …"`.
+  Nothing to repair → `applied=[]` (no-op).
+
+### CLI wiring (`src/cli.ts`)
+
+- `parseDoctorArgs(args)` (exported): hand-rolled loop mirroring
+  `parseAnswerArgs`; reads `--workflow <dir>` / `--workflow=`, `--run <id>` /
+  `--run=`, boolean `--repair`, `--json`; throws clear usage errors when
+  `--workflow` or `--run` is missing.
+- `runs` dispatch: `subcommand === "runs"` → require sub `doctor` (else usage
+  error, exit 1) → `runDoctor` → print `formatReport` (or
+  `JSON.stringify(reportToJson)` with `--json`) → exit `report.ok &&
+  !report.repair?.refused ? 0 : 1`.
+- `printUsage()`: add `runs doctor [--workflow <dir>] --run <id> [--repair]
+  [--json]` to the usage/subcommand list (satisfies "appears in --help" + CLI
+  smoke test).
+
+### Error handling
+
+Doctor is read-only except `--repair`. No async/callback conversion. Repair is
+fail-fast: refusals throw nothing destructive — they short-circuit BEFORE any
+write and return `refused:true`. Backup precedes the atomic rename, so a crash
+mid-repair leaves either the original or the `.bak`+truncated pair, never a
+half-written journal. Unexpected FS errors propagate (no silent swallow).
+
+### TDD order
+
+1. `parseDoctorArgs` (RED→GREEN) — flag parsing + missing-arg errors.
+2. Phase a integrity on fabricated journals (clean exit 0; torn-tail WARNING
+   exit 0; mid-file garbage ERROR exit 1; unknown kind; non-monotonic seq;
+   duplicate event_id).
+3. Phase b invariants (events-after-terminal; undeclared node; attempt without
+   start; cost divergence) using hand-written journal lines.
+4. Phase c (orphan dir; missing declared dir; stale lock).
+5. `--repair` (torn round-trip + byte-identical surviving prefix + `.bak`;
+   refusal on live lock; refusal on mid-file garbage).
+6. `--json` shape.
+7. SRS FR-E83 + index row; then full `deno task check`.
+
+### Verification
+
+- `deno task check 2>&1 | grep -i doctor` for focused iteration; full
+  `deno task check` before commit (fmt, lint, type-check, tests, FR field-set
+  lint, docs budget, CLI smoke, publish dry-run).
+</content>
+</invoke>
